In other news.. I may be quitting my job.

So last friday was my 19th birthday, that was quite the night. We started off at kelly o'brians for dinner. While there they bought me the dumbest looking drink I have ever seen, it was called a leprechaun urine sample. The drink was green and the straw was so long I had to put it on my lap to drink it. the rest of the stay there consisted of various other drink/shots, some were good and some were terrible. I also got the best birthday present ever, a book called the Cannabis Companion. This book is pretty awesome, it has lots of information, rolling guides and some recipes that sound really good.  After that we headed for the willow, this is where the party really started. Mike told all the strippers that it was my birthday, I wont go into what happened after this but I'll say it involved body shots and my face in various places.. next we went to cheetahs. I have no idea how we ended up there but we didn't stay very long, only long enough to roll a joint. Then we headed to gotchas were several more shooters and drinks were had. We hung out there for a bit then headed back to cheetahs to meet some friends from work. While there we saw the hottest stripper I've ever seen(which isn't saying much because this was my first night seeing strippers). My friends then all pitched in a bought me a lap dance from this stripper. again I wont go into what happened in there but I'm sure you can all use your imagination. after that people bought me more shots and by this time it was almost 2 and all the bars were closing so we headed to the pita pit for some more food. By this time I was pretty drunk and spent the whole time in there sitting because it was too hard to stand. After that everyone started heading home so we called a cab and waited.. after half an hour of sitting out in the cold we called them back and asked where our damn cab was, they said it would be there asap. So we waited there for another half an hour and ended up getting a ride home from a completely different cab company. 

All in all it was a really good night and I didn't even have a hang over.

"These magnificent magical creatures are fun, festive, and prone to unexpected mood swings. They keep a very neat lair with tasteful, yet bold use of space and color. These whimsical beasts are thoughtful and perceptive about noticing your new haircut or if you have purchased a new pair of adventure boots even when you are not so thoughtful. They can be counted on to get excited about going shopping and gossiping about that 'awful' new guy one of your friends seems interested in. They enjoy long walks on the beach, weepy films about relationships and eating ice cream directly from the bucket when depressed. You will only be attacked by one if you directly provoke it, or if you have no good answer to the question "Does this make me look fat?" -- which is the same thing."
